[[Category:Olympics|Images]]

{{unreferenced|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox award | name = Olympic Diplomas | current_awards = | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | description = given to top eight finishers in [[Olympic Sports]] | presenter = [[International Olympic Committee]] | | location = | reward = | year = [[1948 Summer Olympics|1948]] | year2 = | holder = | website = [http://www.olympic.org/ www.olympic.org] }}
An '''Olympic diploma''' is a paper certificate awarded to the top eight finishers in competitions at the [[Olympic Games]]. While the top three finishers have received [[Olympic medal|medals]] since the 1896 Olympics, from 1948 onward athletes placing fourth, fifth, and sixth have received certificates, which became officially known as Olympic diplomas; in 1984 diplomas for seventh- and eighth-place finishers were added.
